# Stripe Shop

A minimal Django e-commerce app with Stripe Checkout. Supports single items and multi-item orders with discounts and taxes.

---

## Features

- Browse items and orders on the homepage
- Single-item checkout via Stripe Checkout
- Multi-item orders with optional **discount** (Stripe Coupon) and **tax** (Stripe Tax Rate)
- Dual currency support: **USD** and **EUR** with separate Stripe API keys
- Django Admin for full content management
- Docker-ready

---

## Quick Start (Local)

### 1. Clone and install

```bash
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd stripe_shop

python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate        # Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 2. Configure environment

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Open `.env` and fill in your Stripe keys from [dashboard.stripe.com/apikeys](https://dashboard.stripe.com/apikeys):

```env
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY_USD=sk_test_...
STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY_USD=pk_test_...
SITE_URL=http://localhost:8000   # ← must match the port you run the server on
```

### 3. Run migrations and load sample data

```bash
python manage.py migrate
python manage.py loaddata initial_data.json   # loads sample items, discounts, taxes and an order
```

### 4. Create a superuser and start

```bash
python manage.py createsuperuser
python manage.py runserver
```

Open [http://localhost:8000](http://localhost:8000) — shop is live.  
Admin panel: [http://localhost:8000/admin/](http://localhost:8000/admin/)

---

## Docker Deployment

### 1. Prepare your `.env` file

```bash
cp .env.example .env
# edit .env with your real Stripe keys
```

Set `SITE_URL` to the public address of your server, e.g.:

```env
SITE_URL=https://shop.yourdomain.com
```

### 2. Build and run

```bash
docker compose up --build -d
```

This will automatically:
- Run database migrations
- Load the sample fixture (`initial_data.json`)
- Start the app on port **8000** via Gunicorn

### 3. Create an admin user

```bash
docker compose exec web python manage.py createsuperuser
```

### 4. Access the app

| URL | Description |
|-----|-------------|
| `http://localhost:8000/` | Storefront |
| `http://localhost:8000/admin/` | Admin panel |

### Stopping

```bash
docker compose down
```

---

## Project Structure

```
stripe_shop/          # Django project config
├── settings.py       # All settings, reads from .env
├── urls.py           # Root URL config

shop/                 # Main app
├── models.py         # Item, Order, Discount, Tax
├── views.py          # All views + Stripe Checkout logic
├── urls.py           # App URL config
├── admin.py          # Admin configuration
└── templates/
    ├── base.html     # Base layout
    ├── index.html    # Homepage (items + orders)
    ├── item.html     # Single item page
    ├── order.html    # Order detail + pay button
    ├── success.html  # Post-payment success page
    └── cancel.html   # Cancelled payment page

initial_data.json     # Sample fixture (items, discounts, taxes, order)
Dockerfile
docker-compose.yml
.env.example
```

