## Stripe Setup

### Test card

Use this card number for all test payments:

```
Card:  4242 4242 4242 4242
Date:  any future date
CVC:   any 3 digits
```

### Creating a Coupon (for Discounts)

1. Go to [dashboard.stripe.com/coupons](https://dashboard.stripe.com/coupons)
2. Create a coupon (e.g. `SUMMER10` for 10% off)
3. In Django Admin → **Discounts** → copy the coupon ID into `Stripe Coupon ID`

### Creating a Tax Rate (for Taxes)

1. Go to [dashboard.stripe.com/tax-rates](https://dashboard.stripe.com/tax-rates)
2. Create a tax rate (e.g. VAT 20%)
3. In Django Admin → **Taxes** → copy the tax rate ID (e.g. `txr_xxxxx`) into `Stripe Tax Rate ID`

> The `percent_off` and `percentage` fields in the Django models are display-only. The actual values are always read from Stripe.

---

## Environment Variables Reference

| Variable | Required | Description |
|----------|----------|-------------|
| `SECRET_KEY` | Yes | Django secret key |
| `DEBUG` | No | `True` for dev, `False` for production |
| `ALLOWED_HOSTS` | Yes | Space-separated list of allowed hosts |
| `SITE_URL` | Yes | Full URL of the site — used for Stripe redirect URLs |
| `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY_USD` | Yes | Stripe secret key for USD payments |
| `STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY_USD` | Yes | Stripe publishable key for USD payments |
| `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY_EUR` | No | Stripe secret key for EUR (falls back to USD key) |
| `STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY_EUR` | No | Stripe publishable key for EUR (falls back to USD key) |

